  "prompt": "How do I know who is following me on Snapchat?",
  "response": "Snapchat primarily uses a \"Friends\" system rather than a traditional \"followers\" model found on platforms like Instagram or Twitter. However, with the introduction of Public Profiles and content creators on Snapchat, the concept of followers has become more relevant. Here's how you can manage and view who is connected to you on Snapchat, whether through friends or followers:\n\n### **For Personal Snapchat Accounts (Friends-Based System):**\n\n1. **Open Snapchat:**\n   - Launch the Snapchat app on your smartphone and log in to your account if you aren't already.\n\n2. **Access Your Profile:**\n   - Tap on your profile icon (usually your Bitmoji or a circular icon with your initials) located in the top-left corner of the screen.\n\n3. **View Your Friends List:**\n   - On your profile page, you'll see a section labeled \"Friends.\" Tap on this to view all the friends you've added on Snapchat.\n   - Here, you'll see a list of users who you've mutually added\u2014meaning both parties have accepted each other's friend requests.\n\n4. **Check Recent Adds:**\n   - Scroll through your friends list to see recent additions or use the search bar at the top to find specific friends.\n\n### **For Public Profiles or Content Creators (Followers-Based System):**\n\nIf you have a Public Profile or are using Snapchat as a content creator, you can have followers in addition to friends. Here's how to view and manage your followers:\n\n1. **Ensure You Have a Public Profile:**\n   - Public Profiles are available to creators and businesses. If you don't have one yet, you can convert your account by following Snapchat\u2019s guidelines for setting up a Public Profile.\n\n2. **Access Your Public Profile:**\n   - Open Snapchat and tap on your profile icon in the top-left corner.\n   - If you have a Public Profile, you'll see additional sections related to followers.\n\n3. **View Your Followers:**\n   - On your Public Profile page, look for a \"Followers\" section. This typically displays the number of followers you have.\n   - Tap on the \"Followers\" count to see a detailed list of all the users who are following your Public Profile.\n\n4. **Manage Your Followers:**\n   - While Snapchat doesn't currently offer extensive follower management features (like blocking followers directly from the followers list), you can control who follows you by adjusting your privacy settings or converting back to a personal account if needed.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Notifications for New Friends/Follows:**\n  - Snapchat notifies you when someone adds you as a friend or starts following your Public Profile. Keep an eye on your notifications to stay updated.\n\n- **Privacy Settings:**\n  - To manage who can add you as a friend or follow your Public Profile, go to your profile settings by tapping the gear icon \u2699\ufe0f in the top-right corner of your profile page. Here, you can adjust settings like who can contact you, view your story, or add you as a friend.\n\n- **Understanding \u201cAdded Me\u201d Section:**\n  - Snapchat used to have an \"Added Me\" section where you could see recent additions, but this feature's availability may vary. If available, it can be another way to see who has recently added you.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nWhile Snapchat doesn't use a traditional follower system for personal accounts, Public Profiles do allow for followers, similar to other social media platforms. By following the steps above, you can view and manage your connections on Snapchat effectively. Remember to regularly check your settings to maintain the level of privacy and interaction you desire on the platform.\n\nIf you have any further questions or need assistance with specific features, feel free to ask!",
